|IGR|SARI}}, also known as '''Mayor Carlos Eduardo Krause Airport''',<ref name=AIP /><ref name=WAD /> is an airport in [[Misiones Province]], [[Argentina]] serving the city of [[Puerto Iguaz\u00fa]] and providing access to the nearby [[Iguaz\u00fa Falls]] ({{lang-es|link=no|Cataratas del Iguaz\u00fa}}). It is the easternmost Argentine airport served by scheduled flights.\nThe airport covers an area of {{convert|1804|ha|acre|abbr=on}} and is operated by [[Aeropuertos Argentina 2000]]<ref name=AIP /><ref name=ORSNA />\n\nThe airport is in forested countryside {{convert|16|km|0}} southeast of Puerto Iguaz\u00fa, and {{convert|6|km|0}} south of the falls. The Cataratas Del Iguazu [[VOR-DME]] (Ident: '''IGU''') is located on the field.<ref>{{cite web |title=Cataratas Del Iguazu VOR |url=http://ourairports.com/navaids/IGU/Cataratas_Del_Iguazu_VOR-DME_AR/ |website=Our Airports |accessdate=6 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Airlines and destinations==\n[[File:Aeropuerto Iguaz\u00fa - panoramio.jpg|thumb|alt=View of the terminal ramp and jetways from an aircraft taxiing in to park|Airport terminal, airside]]\n{{Airport-dest-list\n<!-- -->\n|[[Aerol\u00edneas Argentinas]] | [[Aeroparque Jorge Newbery|Buenos Aires\u2013Aeroparque]]\n<!-- -->\n|[[Air Europa]] | [[Silvio Pettirossi International Airport|Asunci\u00f3n]], [[Madrid\u2013Barajas Airport|Madrid]]\n<!-- -->\n|[[Andes L\u00edneas A\u00e9reas]] | [[Aeroparque Jorge Newbery|Buenos Aires\u2013Aeroparque]]<ref>[https://translate.google.com/translate?sl=es&tl=en&js=y&prev=_t&hl=es&ie=UTF-8&u=http%3A%2F%2Fmisionesonline.net%2F2017%2F05%2F03%2Fvuelos-iguazu-buenos-aires-1-040-la-salida-al-mercado-andes-disparo-la-competencia%2F&edit-text=&act=url Misiones Online] \u2013 Andes Airlines to Caratacas</ref>\n<!-- -->\n|[[Austral L\u00edneas A\u00e9reas]] | [[Aeroparque Jorge Newbery|Buenos Aires\u2013Aeroparque]], [[Ministro Pistarini International Airport|Buenos Aires\u2013Ezeiza]], [[Ingeniero Aeron\u00e1utico Ambrosio L.V. Taravella Inte